培训顾问Instructor


Gerald Turner博士是一位专业顾问，是希望通过实施"战略性企业绩效管理" （Strategic Enterprise Performance ManagementSM确  ）实现主营业务转型的组织执行领导团队教练。SEPM是取得预期结果和实现战略的组织变革领导模型。Turner是一位经验丰富的专家，曾任职多种岗位，不仅具有行业知识，而且具有敏锐的流程意识。能够通过有效的战略规划、计划执行和布置、出色运营和绩效管理来实施组织变革。他通过对领导团队的密切合作进行战略开发和实施，实现组织期望的、可持续发展的目标。他同客户一起，使战略目标和组织资源、内部流程相结合，通过技术手段在整个组织内建立一套绩效衡量和管理系统。

他所采用的工具包括平衡计分卡、系统思维法、绩效棱柱、业务整合法、六西格玛、最佳业务模型、康吉、精益生产、全面质量管理、ISO-9001-2002、麦肯 鲍德里奇、最佳业务结构等。他曾担任的职务包括技术总监、TQM总监、首席系统工程师、项目总监、运营副总裁、CEO、COO以及执行管理顾问，责任不断增加。他的国际咨询经验包括：凯捷（Cap Gemini）, 安永（Ernst & Young）和埃森哲 （Accenture）。他最近在从事国内和国际兼并中业务转型和变革进展的研究，包括欧洲、中东、南美、亚洲、环太平洋地区、美国、墨西哥和加拿大。

Turner博士获得电子电气学学士学位、机械工程学学士学位；互联网系统工程硕士和系统管理EMBA，以及营运战略与管理博士学位。现任得克萨斯大学达拉斯学MBA特邀讲师，主讲战略性项目管理。他同时还是认证工程师和认证项目经理。

Gerald Turner is a professional consultant, advisor and coach to executive leadership teams in organizations that want to initiate major business transformation through Strategic Enterprise Performance ManagementSM - the organizational change leadership model for results attainment and strategy realization. He is a seasoned professional who has "been there, done that" and has both the business industry expertise and process acumen to deliver organizational change through effective strategic planning, plan execution and deployment, operational excellence and performance management. He delivers sustainable results by working closely with leadership teams to develop and execute strategies toward realization of the desired future state. He then partners with customers to align strategic objectives with organizational resources, internal processes and enabling technologies to implement an enterprise-wide performance measurement and management system. 
Tools of his trade include Balanced Scorecard, Systems Thinking ApproachSM, Performance Prism, Business Integration Methodology, Six Sigma, Business Excellence Model, Kaizen, Lean Manufacturing, TQM, ISO-9001:2002, Malcolm Baldrige, Business Excellence ArchitectureSM, etc. He has held positions of increasing responsibility including technology director, TQM director, chief systems engineer, program director, VP of operations, CEO, COO and executive management consultant. His experience within global management consulting includes Cap Gemini, Ernst & Young, and Accenture. His most recent engagements have included development of state-of-the-art organizational transformation and change programs for major domestic and international customers in emerging global markets including Europe, Middle East, South America, Asia, Pacific Rim, United States, Mexico and Canada. 
Dr. Turner earned BSEE and BSME degrees, an MSIE in Industrial Systems Engineering, an Executive MBA in Systems Management, and a Ph.D. in Operations Strategy and Management. He is presently a guest lecturer in the MBA program at the University of Texas at Dallas in the area of Strategic Program-Project Management. He is also a Registered Professional Engineer (PE) and Certified Program Manager (CPM).

