Objectives: Understand the evolution of measurement and strategic management systems; define common terms; Learn the reasons for adopting a balanced scorecard system; identify the six steps needed to build a scorecard system and the three steps needed to implement these systems; describe what a scorecard system is and is not;  identify challenges that need to be overcome; discuss indicators of successful systems; discuss time periods for a scorecard project; contrast the differences and similarities in scorecard systems for different organizations; discuss a typical BSC development cycle.）
 
